%kkaxis 'Reorient Data on the Width, Height, and Depth Axes'
% This MatLab function was automatically generated by a converter (KhorosToMatLab) from the Khoros kaxis.pane file
%
% Parameters: 
% InputFile: i 'Input ', required: 'input data object'
% OutputFile: o 'Output', required: 'resulting data object'
% Toggle: ww 'Width', default: 0: 'assign input width data to output width axis'
% Toggle: wh 'Height', default: 0: 'Assign input width data to output height axis'
% Toggle: wd 'Depth', default: 0: 'Assign input width data to output depth axis'
% Toggle: hw 'Width', default: 0: 'Assign input height data to output width axis'
% Toggle: hh 'Height', default: 0: 'Assign input height data to output height axis'
% Toggle: hd 'Depth', default: 0: 'Assign input height data to output depth axis'
% Toggle: dw 'Width', default: 0: 'Assign input depth data to output width axis'
% Toggle: dh 'Height', default: 0: 'Assign input depth data to output height axis'
% Toggle: dd 'Depth', default: 0: 'Assign input depth data to output depth axis'
%
% Example: o = kkaxis(i, {'i','';'o','';'ww',0;'wh',0;'wd',0;'hw',0;'hh',0;'hd',0;'dw',0;'dh',0;'dd',0})
%
% Khoros helpfile follows below:
%
%  PROGRAM
% kaxis - Reorient Data on the Width, Height, and Depth Axes
%
%  DESCRIPTION
% kaxis reorients the input data to the specified output axes.
% For example, if the input data has the dimensions
% width = 100, height = 200 and depth = 20, and the user specifies
% that the input height data be assigned to the output width axis
% and the input width data be assigned to the output height axis,
% then the data would be reassigned so that the output dimensions
% would be width = 200, height = 100, depth = 20.  Note that only one input
% axis may be assigned to each output axis.
% 
% The axis orientation is performed on value, mask, and location data,
% whenever they exist in the input object.  The output data type is 
% the same as the input data type.  If map or time data exist, they
% are directly transferred to the output object, since they are not 
% affected by width, height, or depth axis reassignments.
%
%  
%
%  EXAMPLES
%
%  "SEE ALSO"
% korient
%
%  RESTRICTIONS 
%
%  REFERENCES 
%
